        "<strong>Croscarmellose Sodium (CCS)</strong> (CAS 74811-65-7) is an internally cross-linked sodium carboxymethyl cellulose produced by chemically cross-linking sodium CMC under controlled conditions to render the polymer permanently insoluble in water. Unlike sodium CMC which dissolves in water, cross-linked CCS swells 4–8 times its original volume upon hydration while remaining insoluble — generating both capillary wicking action and internal swelling pressure that rapidly ruptures tablet matrices. It is classified as a <strong>superdisintegrant</strong> — the most efficient category of tablet disintegrant, and the reference standard against which all other superdisintegrants are benchmarked.<br><br>CCS is fully multi-compendial, appearing in the <strong>USP/NF</strong>, <strong>Ph.Eur. 9.0</strong>, <strong>BP</strong>, and <strong>JP XVII</strong>. Key pharmacopoeial specifications: pH 5.0–7.0 (1% aqueous dispersion), sodium content 7.3–10.8% (dry basis), loss on drying ≤ 10.0%, settling volume ≥ 10.0 mL, and heavy metals ≤ 20 ppm. Microbiological limits require total aerobic count ≤ 1,000 CFU/g and absence of <em>E. coli</em> and <em>Salmonella</em>.<br><br>In the <strong>pharmaceutical industry</strong>, CCS is used at 0.5–5% w/w in compressed tablets (WG, DC, dry granulation), hard gelatin and HPMC capsule fills (10–25% of fill weight), orally disintegrating tablets (ODT), chewable tablets, dispersible tablets, and semi-effervescent dosage forms. Present in thousands of global drug registrations covering analgesics, antibiotics, cardiovascular drugs, antidiabetics, antacids, antihistamines, and multivitamins.<br><br>In the <strong>nutraceutical and dietary supplement industry</strong>, CCS (nutraceutical grade) is used in vitamin tablets, mineral supplement tablets, herbal extract tablets, sports nutrition tablets, probiotic tablets, and enzyme supplement formulations at dosages of 0.5–4% w/w. Fast disintegration improves consumer perception, label claim substantiation, and bioavailability test outcomes.<br><br><strong>VIVINE International</strong> supplies CCS in standard pharmaceutical grade, fine particle grade, nutraceutical grade, and capsule fill grade — all USP/NF and Ph.Eur. compliant. TDS, SDS, COA, FDA DMF reference letters, and impurity profiles available. Halal and Kosher certification available.",
